text: <@U4V5EHQ2G>, I’m glad i wasn’t the only one who thought of Morophon Knights. I’ve been struggling to figure out the colors I want for my Knight deck since Mardu didn’t work, but having access to Kindred Discovery and Overrun effects and stuff really feels like it shores up my issues with the tribe.
Yeah, the biggest problem is always how to win, and although green overruns aren't the most creative solution, it's better than chip damage
If you’re playing Knights, I think you already get creativity points for deck construction. You can lose a few if your wincon is Triumph if the Hordes or whatever.
I’ll probably be putting the deck together over the next few weeks. If you put yours together, let me know! I’d love to compare lists!
I'm just kind of mad and kind of honored that apparently me and JLK brewed the exact same deck the second we saw Morophon.
You put in two avatars and 25 popular utility creatures and called it a tribal deck, too?
JLK is king of the generic good stuff
Avatars is sweet. That whole Lorwyn/Shadowmoor cycle was awesome.
All of which he played, for the record. Nah, avatars was a good one for Morophon because of the sheer amount of WUBRG free ones.
